# Flexibility-Oriented Stochastic Unit Commitment (FSUC)

This repository implements a two-stage stochastic unit commitment model with integrated storage dynamics and flexibility-aware operation.

## Model Features

- Two-stage stochastic optimization (scenario-based uncertainty)
- Unit commitment with startup decisions
- Ramp constraints and operational limits
- Energy storage modeling (SOC dynamics, efficiency)
- Load shedding with Value of Lost Load (VOLL)
- Flexibility shortage quantification

## Motivation

High renewable penetration introduces variability and uncertainty in power systems. This model captures system flexibility limitations and quantifies the ability of generation and storage resources to meet demand under uncertainty.

## Methodology

The model is formulated as a mixed-integer linear program (MILP) using Pyomo and solved with GLPK.

## How to Run

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python main.py
